President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring November 2012 as National Alzheimer's Disease Awareness Month in the United States. The proclamation acknowledges the devastating effects of Alzheimer's disease on individuals and their families, highlighting the progressive mental and physical impairments caused by the illness. The proclamation emphasizes the need for a comprehensive and collaborative approach to address Alzheimer's disease, including investments in research, clinical trials, and support for caregivers. It also encourages Americans to learn more about the disease and offer their support to those affected.